wpt.desc: Northwood Hill Cache by dndsnel1210 adopted by Kin9sPanK, Traditional Cache (2/2.5)

groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:name: Northwood Hill Cache
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:short_description: This cache is a Army Decon Container. The area can get a bit overgrown in the summer so I would wear long pants at that time of year. A slight hill will not allow biking to the actual cache site. Some bushwhacking may be required. The cache is well hidden. Please rehide as well or better.
groundspeak:cache.groundspeak:long_description:
The cache is filled with a bunch of neat small items that were rescued from the previous cache container. The new cache container is a Army Decon Container. It will happily accept geocoins and small travelbugs. Decon Container lids seal with an audible snap. No snap, no seal. Please do not overstuff the container and insure that the lid is on tight before rehiding the cache.
Have fun!!
